.TH PRODBOX_nuke 1
.SH NAME
prodbox-nuke \- Total teardown of every prodbox-owned AWS resource (operator-only)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B prodbox nuke
.SH DESCRIPTION
The only sanctioned path to destroy long-lived shared infrastructure (`aws-ses`, the long-lived `pulumi_state_backend` bucket) transitively. TTY-only; refuses non-interactive contexts. Requires the typed confirmation literal `NUKE EVERYTHING`. No `--yes` shorthand by design. `--dry-run` renders the plan without mutating any state.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--dry-run\fR
Render the teardown plan without mutating state
.TP
\fB--plan-file\fR <PATH>
Write the rendered plan to a file
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
\fBprodbox nuke --dry-run\fR
Render the total-teardown plan.
